{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Summary\nWhen a synced local ticket is archived or moved to status `deleted`, its bound Jira issue is left live (e.g. \"To Do\") indefinitely. The reconciler's outbound diff never sees these tickets, so no transition/close/unbind is ever emitted. Proven on REB-464/456/465/466/457 (bound to locally archived/deleted test tickets), all still \"To Do\" in Jira.\n\n## Root Cause (two filter layers, an unintended gap)\n- Layer 1 (archived): the reconciler builds its local snapshot via `rebar list --full` (`reconcile.py:455`) with no `--include-archived`; `reducer/_api.py:234` drops `archived=True`. Archived tickets never enter the diff.\n- Layer 2 (deleted): deleted-status tickets survive the snapshot but are skipped in the differ loop (`outbound_differ.py:537-540`, `excluded_statuses={archived,deleted}`).\n- Smoking gun: `outbound_fields.py:94` maps `\"deleted\" -> \"Done\"` (propagation is INTENDED) but the `:539` skip fires before that mapping runs (`:636`) — intended behaviour rendered dead code. `OutboundMutation` declares a `\"delete\"` action (`outbound_differ.py:245`) but nothing ever constructs one. Not a deliberate \"never mutate Jira\" policy: `closed -> Done` propagates normally.\n- Runtime proof: `rebar list --full` returns 0 for the archived id vs 1 with `--include-archived`; a `reconcile --mode dry-run` (249 mutations over 606 issues) plans nothing for any of these keys.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Sync a local ticket to Jira (binding confirmed).\n2. Archive it, or transition it to `deleted` locally.\n3. Run `rebar reconcile --mode dry-run`.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: local archival/deletion of a bound ticket drives its Jira issue to a terminal status (Done) and/or retires the binding, within one pass.\n- Actual: no mutation is planned; the Jira issue is stranded live forever.\n\n## Proposed design (perf-safe, binding-driven)\nDrive terminal-transition detection from the BINDING STORE, not a full archived-ticket scan, so cost scales with the number of *synced* tickets (~606), never with the total number of archived tickets:\n- Each pass compute `missing = bindings.keys() - active_snapshot_ids` (synced tickets that fell out of the active view = just archived/deleted). Cheap set-diff over ~606 bindings.\n- For only those ids, do a targeted state read and emit the already-wired terminal transition (`deleted`/`archived -> Done`) via `_LOCAL_TO_JIRA_STATUS` + `_diff_fields`.\n- Idempotency: once Jira == Done the field-diff is empty (near-zero steady-state cost); optionally retire the binding after the terminal transition so it leaves the working set. Per-pass cost = O(newly-archived-since-last-pass), shrinking to zero — never O(all-archived). Do NOT switch the full snapshot to `--include-archived`.\n- Unifies with the class-C binding GC (same binding-store iteration).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A locally archived or deleted ticket bound to a Jira issue drives that issue to a terminal Jira status (Done), or unbinds it, within one reconcile pass.\n- [ ] Detection is bounded by #bindings / #newly-archived, not total archived-ticket count (no full `--include-archived` snapshot per pass); documented with a perf note/test.\n- [ ] The dead `_LOCAL_TO_JIRA_STATUS[\"deleted\"]=\"Done\"` mapping becomes reachable (or is replaced by an explicit terminal-transition path).\n- [ ] A test binds a ticket, archives/deletes it locally, runs a pass, and asserts the Jira issue transitions to Done (RED before fix).\n- [ ] The concrete drift (REB-464/456/465/466/457) reconciles after the fix.\n\n## Notes\nDiscovered comparing Jira REB vs the local store. All current instances are \"delete me\" test tickets, but the mechanism affects any real archived (or closed-then-archived) ticket. `bridge_fsck` does not detect this (see the class-D ticket). Files: `outbound_differ.py`, `outbound_fields.py`, `reconcile.py`, `reducer/_api.py`.\n\n## Guardrails (must-preserve — prior-art + archaeology; folds in the corrected plan)\nApproved policy: local archive/delete drives the Jira issue to a terminal status (Done). But:\n- [ ] Drive the terminal transition from the per-binding BASELINE + binding-store walk, NOT from snapshot membership; act only on a CONFIRMED terminal/404 (grace-counted), never on snapshot-absence (L13/L16/L17).\n- [ ] Close the bidir loop: add `archived` to the reverse status map AND the single-pass bidir suppression, so inbound reading Jira `Done` does not flip local `archived -> closed` (L21/L3; `inbound_translate.py:121`). Today `archived` maps nowhere on the reverse path.\n- [ ] Gate the whole class behind the circuit breaker (refuse a pass that would terminal-transition/retire > N% of bindings) [prior art: Argo `allowEmpty`].\n- [ ] Preserve `note_absent` grace + reversible retirement (L14/L15); a local-archive retirement must not corrupt the `absent_404_count` machinery.\n- [ ] Unify with class C (13eb): one binding-store loop heals terminal transitions and GCs dead bindings.\n- [ ] Parity is proven by the CONVERGENCE property (re-reconcile after the heal yields zero actions), not by an enumerated case."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783078754273374001,"uuid":"6cac7d3e-ef8d-42cf-bf3b-eef2f972e8f9"}